<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec_intensity-patterns" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Intensity Patterns</title>
	
			<subsubsection>
	<title>Warm-up Activities</title>
			<activity>
			<title>Intensity to Loudness</title>
			<p></p>
			  <p>How loud is a noise that has an intensity of <m>I = 100 I_0</m>?</p>
			</activity>

			<activity>
			<title>Speaking to a Friend</title>
			<p></p>
			  <p>Speaking to your friend involves sound at about 60 dB. How much bigger is the intensity of a sound at 80 dB?

			  </p>
			</activity>

			<activity>
			<title>The Vacuum Cleaner</title>
			<statement>
			<p></p>
			  <p>If a vacuum cleaner makes a sound of 75 dB from a distance of 1 m away, how far away must you stand from the vacuum cleaner for the sound to drop to a level of 25 dB (a whisper)?
			  </p>
			</statement>
			<hint>
				<p>
					Write a symbolic expression for the sound level in terms of the distance from the source.
				</p>
			</hint>
			</activity>

		</subsubsection>

      <subsubsection>
		<title>Intensity Pattern Activities</title>
		<activity>
			<title>Sound Detectors</title>
			<introduction>
				<p>
					
				</p>
				<p>
					A source produces a sound with power P. It sits across from a wall of sound detectors a distance <m>L</m> away, as shown below. The sound detectors are separated from each other by a distance <m>s</m>.
				</p>
				<figure xml:id="fig_sound-detectors">
<title>Sound Detectors Figure</title>
    	<caption>
	Five speakers near a source of sound waves.
	</caption>
    	<image source="sound-detectors.png" width = "75%" ></image>
</figure>	
			</introduction>
			<task>
				<statement>
					<p>
						Which speaker(s) will detect the loudest sound?
					</p>
				</statement>
			</task>
			<task>
				<statement>
					<p>
						Which speaker(s) will detect the faintest sound?
					</p>
				</statement>
			</task>
			<task>
				<statement>
					<p>
						Determine a symbolic expression for the intensity of the sound at point A. 
					</p>
				</statement>
			</task>
			<task>
				<statement>
					<p>
						What if the wall was made up of an infinite number of detectors? What would a graph of the intensity vs. vertical position look like?
					</p>
				</statement>
			</task>
		</activity>
	  </subsubsection>
	
</section>

